HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1043
By Sexton
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend comedian and Old
Hickory native Nate Bargatze.
WHEREAS, it is the privilege of the members of this General Assembly to recognize
those outstanding Tennesseans whose natural talent and devotion to their craft have vaulted
them to the very pinnacle of success; and
WHEREAS, hailed as "The Nicest Man in Stand-Up" by The Atlantic, Nate Bargatze has
become a household name in recent years, with his trademark everyman, family-friendly
standup routines, at once relatable and hilarious, being streamed for over sixty-two million hours
globally across multiple platforms; and
WHEREAS, his first solo one-hour Netflix special, The Tennessee Kid, premiered in
2019 to rave reviews, and his 2021 follow-up Netflix special, The Greatest Average American,
received critical acclaim and a Grammy nomination for Best Comedy Album; his third one-hour
special, Hello World, premiered on Amazon Prime in 2023 and holds the record as the outlet's
most-streamed original comedy special in its first twenty-eight days of viewership; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, Mr. Bargatze returned to Netflix with a two stand-up special deal,
the first of which, Your Friend, Nate Bargatze, premiered on December 24, 2024, and landed in
the Top 10 most-watched shows globally for two weeks; in the spring of 2025, it was the most
watched standup special on Netflix in the past fifty-two weeks, with his two previous Netflix
specials listed at No. 16 and No. 14 on the fifty-two-week chart, even though they premiered six
and four years earlier, respectively; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Bargatze is currently the top-earning comedian in the world according to
Pollstar's recent report and twelfth in overall live-tour ticket sales, putting him in the company of
HJR1043
014136
- 1 -

Coldplay, Madonna, and U2. Billboard recently announced that Bargatze set a new record for
the biggest one-year gross by a comedy performer in history; and
WHEREAS, in 2023, Bargatze unveiled Nateland Entertainment, a family-friendly
content company through which he produces standup comedy specials, showcases, sketches,
and scripted episodic content for film, television, podcasts, music, and more; and
WHEREAS, in May 2025, he published his highly anticipated first book, Big Dumb Eyes:
Stories From A Simpler Mind, which instantly became the New York Times No. 1 best-selling
book and remained on the best-seller list for eleven weeks; and
WHEREAS, he has also proven himself a compelling host, delivering the opening
monologue in Studio 8H with Saturday Night Live twice, first in 2023 and again in 2024, each
time to rave reviews and enthusiastic reception by audiences; as host of the seventy-seventh
Primetime Emmy Awards on CBS in 2024, he drew the show's largest audience in four years;
and
WHEREAS, his most recent hosting gig is with The Greatest Average American, a trivia
show that premiered on February 25, 2026, on ABC and Hulu; co-created and executive
produced by Mr. Bargatze and John Quinn (Price is Right), the show celebrates the power of
being perfectly average and boasts a grand prize of $67,920—the average American salary;
and
WHEREAS, he will also be making his silver-screen debut in 2026 with The
Breadwinner, a family-friendly comedy with TriStar Pictures that he co-wrote and served as
executive producer; the film co-stars Mandy Moore, Colin Jost, Will Forte, and Kumail Nanjiani
and is directed by Emmy winner Eric Appel; and
WHEREAS, despite his many ventures, Nate Bargatze continues to wow audiences with
his original standup routines—his Be Funny tour grossed upwards of $88 million, making him
the top-grossing comedian of 2024; the tour broke ticket and attendance records across the
- 2 - 014136

country, including in his home state, where he became the only comedian ever to sell out three
consecutive performances at Bridgestone Arena in Nashville; and
WHEREAS, currently on his 2025 Big Dumb Eyes World Tour, Nate Bargatze continues
to break venue attendance and ticket sales records; and
WHEREAS, throughout his meteoric rise, Nate Bargatze, a self-noted native of Old
Hickory, has shown that authenticity resonates across geographic and cultural divides and that
being average is in itself a quite extraordinary thing; and
WHEREAS, a two-time Grammy- and Emmy-nominated comedian, New York Times No.
1 bestselling author, podcaster, director, and producer, Mr. Bargatze has reached heights to
which few individuals in comedy have ascended, and fewer still have done so while remaining
true to themselves and exhibiting the utmost integrity, humility, and pride in who they are and
where they come from; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend comedian Nate Bargatze, a Tennessee kid who
made good, and one of whom the Volunteer State is exceedingly proud.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
